  • Method Details

    • setUp

      @BeforeEach void setUp() throws IOException
      Sets up a temporary conference file before each test. The file contains a conference name, multiple sessions with assigned items, and unassigned items.
      Throws:
      IOException - if there is a problem creating the temporary file

    • testReadConferenceFileValid

      @Test void testReadConferenceFileValid()
      Tests that ConferenceReader correctly reads a valid conference file. Verifies sessions, assigned accepted items, unassigned items, and remaining capacities.

    • testReadConferenceFileNonExistent

      @Test void testReadConferenceFileNonExistent()
      Tests that reading a non-existent conference file throws IllegalArgumentException.

    • testReadConferenceFileNull

      @Test void testReadConferenceFileNull()
      Tests that reading a null conference file throws IllegalArgumentException.

    • testProcessAcceptedItemThroughFile

      @Test void testProcessAcceptedItemThroughFile() throws Exception
      Tests reading a conference file with unassigned items. Verifies that unknown item types are ignored and valid items are correctly added as unassigned.
      Throws:
      Exception - if file creation fails

    • testProcessAcceptedItemTypes

      @Test void testProcessAcceptedItemTypes() throws Exception
      Tests that only valid accepted item types (Paper, Panel, LightningTalk) are added from the file. Verifies that unknown types are ignored. Also checks default durations for Panel and LightningTalk.
      Throws:
      Exception - if file creation fails
